The paper discusses the validation of requirements, which is a key aspect of software engineering (cs.SE). It also focuses on the use of model-based representation formats, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and requirements engineering (cs.RE). The paper also mentions the use of annotations, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the integration of inconsistent requirements, which is relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
